msgid "Sā purimaṃ pādaṃ suppatiṭṭhitaṃ patiṭṭhāpetvā pacchimaṃ pādaṃ uddhareyya. "
msgstr "She’d take a step with a fore-hoof; and after it was properly set down, she’d lift up a hind-hoof. "

msgctxt "an9.35:3.5"
msgid "Sā agatapubbañceva disaṃ gaccheyya, akhāditapubbāni ca tiṇāni khādeyya, apītapubbāni ca pānīyāni piveyya. "
msgstr "She’d go somewhere she’d never been before, and eat grass and drink water that she’d never tried before. "

msgctxt "an9.35:3.6"
msgid "Yasmiṃ cassā padese ṭhitāya evamassa: "
msgstr "And she’d return safely to the place she had started from. "

msgctxt "an9.35:3.7"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ agatapubbañceva disaṃ gaccheyyaṃ, akhāditapubbāni ca tiṇāni khādeyyaṃ, apītapubbāni ca pānīyāni piveyyan’ti tañca padesaṃ sotthinā paccāgaccheyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an9.35:3.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an9.35:3.9"
msgid "Tathā hi sā, bhikkhave, gāvī pabbateyyā paṇḍitā byattā khettaññū kusalā visame pabbate carituṃ. "
msgstr "Because that mountain cow was astute, competent, skillful, and used common sense when roaming on rugged mountains. "

msgctxt "an9.35:3.10"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhikkhu paṇḍito byatto khettaññū kusalo vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "In the same way, some astute, competent, skillful mendicant, using common sense, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "an9.35:3.11"
msgid "So taṃ nimittaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti svādhiṭṭhitaṃ adhiṭṭhāti. "
msgstr "They cultivate, develop, and make much of that foundation, ensuring that it’s properly stabilized. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an9.35:4.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "They think, "

msgctxt "an9.35:4.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, enter and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:4.3"
msgid "So dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ anabhihiṃsamāno vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Without charging at the second absorption, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption. "

msgctxt "an9.35:4.4"
msgid "So taṃ nimittaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti svādhiṭṭhitaṃ adhiṭṭhāti. "
msgstr "They cultivate, develop, and make much of that foundation, ensuring that it’s properly stabilized. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.420, sc5
msgctxt "an9.35:5.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "They think, "

msgctxt "an9.35:5.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca vihareyyaṃ sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeyyaṃ yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti—upekkhako satimā sukhavihārīti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, with the fading away of rapture, enter and remain in the third absorption, where I will meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, “Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.”’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:5.3"
msgid "So tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ anabhihiṃsamāno pītiyā ca virāgā … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Without charging at the third absorption, with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third absorption. "

msgctxt "an9.35:5.4"
msgid "So taṃ nimittaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti svādhiṭṭhitaṃ adhiṭṭhāti. "
msgstr "They cultivate, develop, and make much of that foundation, ensuring that it’s properly stabilized. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an9.35:6.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "They think, "

msgctxt "an9.35:6.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, with the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness and sadness, enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:6.3"
msgid "So catutthaṃ jhānaṃ anabhihiṃsamāno sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Without charging at the fourth absorption, with the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness and sadness, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "an9.35:6.4"
msgid "So taṃ nimittaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti svādhiṭṭhitaṃ adhiṭṭhāti. "
msgstr "They cultivate, develop, and make much of that foundation, ensuring that it’s properly stabilized. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an9.35:7.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "They think, "

msgctxt "an9.35:7.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ananto ākāsoti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that “space is infinite”, enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:7.3"
msgid "So ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ anabhihiṃsamāno sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā … pe … ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Without charging at the dimension of infinite space, with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space. "

msgctxt "an9.35:7.4"
msgid "So taṃ nimittaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti svādhiṭṭhitaṃ adhiṭṭhāti. "
msgstr "They cultivate, develop, and make much of that foundation, ensuring that it’s properly stabilized. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an9.35:8.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "They think, "

msgctxt "an9.35:8.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma anantaṃ viññāṇanti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that “consciousness is infinite”, enter and remain in the dimension of infinite consciousness.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:8.3"
msgid "So viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ anabhihiṃsamāno sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Without charging at the dimension of infinite consciousness, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite consciousness. "

msgctxt "an9.35:8.4"
msgid "So taṃ nimittaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti svādhiṭṭhitaṃ adhiṭṭhāti. "
msgstr "They cultivate, develop, and make much of that foundation, ensuring that it’s properly stabilized. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an9.35:9.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "They think, "

msgctxt "an9.35:9.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma natthi kiñcīti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that “there is nothing at all”, enter and remain in the dimension of nothingness.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:9.3"
msgid "So ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ anabhihiṃsamāno sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Without charging at the dimension of nothingness, they enter and remain in the dimension of nothingness. "

msgctxt "an9.35:9.4"
msgid "So taṃ nimittaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti svādhiṭṭhitaṃ adhiṭṭhāti. "
msgstr "They cultivate, develop, and make much of that foundation, ensuring that it’s properly stabilized. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.421, sc10
msgctxt "an9.35:10.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "They think, "

msgctxt "an9.35:10.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, enter and remain in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:10.3"
msgid "So nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ anabhihiṃsamāno sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Without charging at the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, they enter and remain in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. "

msgctxt "an9.35:10.4"
msgid "So taṃ nimittaṃ āsevati bhāveti bahulīkaroti svādhiṭṭhitaṃ adhiṭṭhāti. "
msgstr "They cultivate, develop, and make much of that foundation, ensuring that it’s properly stabilized. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an9.35:11.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "They think, "

msgctxt "an9.35:11.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:11.3"
msgid "So saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ anabhihiṃsamāno sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Without charging at the cessation of perception and feeling, they enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an9.35:12.1"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu taṃ tadeva samāpattiṃ samāpajjatipi vuṭṭhātipi, tassa mudu cittaṃ hoti kammaññaṃ. "
msgstr "When a mendicant enters and emerges from all these attainments, their mind becomes pliable and workable. "

msgctxt "an9.35:12.2"
msgid "Mudunā kammaññena cittena appamāṇo samādhi hoti subhāvito. "
msgstr "With a pliable and workable mind, their immersion becomes limitless and well developed. "

msgctxt "an9.35:12.3"
msgid "So appamāṇena samādhinā subhāvitena yassa yassa abhiññāsacchikaraṇīyassa dhammassa cittaṃ abhininnāmeti abhiññāsacchikiriyāya tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇāti sati sati āyatane. "
msgstr "They become capable of realizing anything that can be realized by insight to which they extend the mind, in each and every case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "an9.35:13.1"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati: ‘anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhaveyyaṃ—ekopi hutvā bahudhā assaṃ, bahudhāpi hutvā eko assaṃ … pe … yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteyyan’ti, "
msgstr "They might wish: ‘May I wield the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying myself and becoming one again … controlling my body as far as the Brahmā realm.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:13.2"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇāti sati sati āyatane. "
msgstr "They are capable of realizing it, in each and every case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an9.35:14.1"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati: ‘dibbāya sotadhātuyā … pe … "
msgstr "They might wish: ‘With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, may I hear both kinds of sounds, human and divine, whether near or far.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:14.2"
msgid "sati sati āyatane. "
msgstr "They are capable of realizing it, in each and every case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "an9.35:15.1"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati: ‘parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajāneyyaṃ, sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ sarāgaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ vītarāgaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ sadosaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vītadosaṃ vā cittaṃ vītadosaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, samohaṃ vā cittaṃ samohaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vītamohaṃ vā cittaṃ … saṅkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ … vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ … mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ … amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ … sauttaraṃ vā cittaṃ … anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ … samāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ … asamāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ … vimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ … avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ avimuttaṃ cittanti pajāneyyan’ti, "
msgstr "They might wish: ‘May I understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having comprehended them with my mind. May I understand mind with greed as “mind with greed”, and mind without greed as “mind without greed”; mind with hate as “mind with hate”, and mind without hate as “mind without hate”; mind with delusion as “mind with delusion”, and mind without delusion as “mind without delusion”; constricted mind … scattered mind … expansive mind … unexpansive mind … mind that is not supreme … mind that is supreme … mind immersed in samādhi … mind not immersed in samādhi … freed mind … and unfreed mind as “unfreed mind”.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:15.2"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇāti sati sati āyatane. "
msgstr "They are capable of realizing it, in each and every case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an9.35:16.1"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati: ‘anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussareyyaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussareyyan’ti, "
msgstr "They might wish: ‘May I recollect many kinds of past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. They remember: “There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.” May I recollect my many past lives, with features and details.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:16.2"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇāti sati sati āyatane. "
msgstr "They’re capable of realizing it, in each and every case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.422, sc17
msgctxt "an9.35:17.1"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati: ‘dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajāneyyan’ti "
msgstr "They might wish: ‘With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, may I see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place—and understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:17.2"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇāti sati sati āyatane. "
msgstr "They’re capable of realizing it, in each and every case. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "an9.35:18.1"
msgid "So sace ākaṅkhati: ‘āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyan’ti, "
msgstr "They might wish: ‘May I realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.’ "

msgctxt "an9.35:18.2"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇāti sati sati āyatane”ti. "
msgstr "They’re capable of realizing it, in each and every case.” "

